<p class="MsoNormal" align="center"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color:black"><font face="Arial" size="2"><b><span style="color: black">Movie</span></b></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="left"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color:black"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="color: black">This
animation represents 90 minutes, compressed to only 9 seconds. I used the free tool <a href="http://home.hccnet.nl/s.vd.palen/index.html" target="_blank">
PhotoLapse</a> by Stephan van der Palen to create a video of 45 rendered images,
taken with an
interval of 2 minutes at the day of the equinox.</span></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center"> <a href="3d-kukulcan%20equinox.avi"><img border="0" src="3d-kukulcan%20equinox%2045.jpg"></a></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center"><span lang="NL-BE" style="mso-ansi-language:NL-BE"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="mso-ansi-language: NL-BE">Click
on the movie to see how the shadow forms the snake's body (AVI, 943kB).<br>Or watch <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/erikdierkx?feature=mhum#p/u/12/L28sILLGckY" target="_blank">3D Simulation of Equinox Snake Shadow on Kukulcan Pyramid</a> on Youtube.</span></font></span></p>
<hr>

    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="703" height="27" colspan="3">

<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="margin-bottom: -17"><span style="mso-ansi-language: NL-BE" lang="NL-BE"><b><font face="Arial" color="#800000" size="2">3D
Model</font></b></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="margin-bottom: -17"><span lang="NL-BE" style="mso-ansi-language:NL-BE"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="mso-ansi-language: NL-BE"><a href="kukulcan_dxf.zip"><img border="0" src="el%20castillo.bmp" width="73" height="54"></a></span></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="margin-bottom: -17"><span style="mso-ansi-language: NL-BE" lang="NL-BE"><b><font face="Arial" color="#800000" size="2">free
download dxf</font></b></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="margin-bottom: -17">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="left" style="margin-bottom: -17"><span style="mso-ansi-language: NL-BE" lang="NL-BE"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="mso-ansi-language: NL-BE">To
download the basic model of the Kukulcan pyramid which I used for these
renderings (AutoCAD 2000 DXF, 3D-solid, no textures, zipped 1.667kB) for free: right-click on the
image above, then choose &quot;Save target as...&quot;</span></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="left" style="margin-bottom: -17">&nbsp;</p>
